00:40:31.590 --> 00:40:38.250
Because when you are so
ingrained in that diet culture,

00:40:38.250 --> 00:40:41.440
you feel like a lot of your
identity is wrapped up in it.

00:40:41.440 --> 00:40:43.710
So I don't really know
who I was without a diet

00:40:43.710 --> 00:40:45.840
because it consumed
so much of my life.

00:40:45.840 --> 00:40:49.290
So giving myself that freedom
to break free from that

00:40:49.290 --> 00:40:51.180
felt like I was
rediscovering who I was

00:40:51.180 --> 00:40:53.640
and almost creating a
new identity for myself.

00:40:53.640 --> 00:40:55.590
Because it had taken
up so much head space

00:40:55.590 --> 00:40:57.850
that when I got rid of that,
I was like, oh, my God.

00:40:57.850 --> 00:41:00.510
I don't know what to
do with myself anymore.

00:41:00.510 --> 00:41:02.920
It was like a full-time
job for me, dieting.

00:41:02.920 --> 00:41:06.270
So coming out of that was
definitely a bumpy road.

00:41:06.270 --> 00:41:11.200
But I just kept focusing on,
I'm getting my life back here.

00:41:11.200 --> 00:41:13.620
So even though to begin
with I gained weight,

00:41:13.620 --> 00:41:16.020
I also gained my life back,
which was so much more

00:41:16.020 --> 00:41:17.730
important to me.

00:41:17.730 --> 00:41:20.511
But yeah, I definitely
had to figure out

00:41:20.511 --> 00:41:22.260
all of these different
beliefs and stories

00:41:22.260 --> 00:41:25.439
that I was telling myself
around different diets and food

00:41:25.439 --> 00:41:26.730
and the people that I followed.

00:41:26.730 --> 00:41:28.140
I had to unfollow
a lot of people

00:41:28.140 --> 00:41:31.347
that were projecting their
beliefs out onto social media.

00:41:31.347 --> 00:41:33.055
And I was like, that's
not helpful for me

00:41:33.055 --> 00:41:34.290
for where I'm at right now.

00:41:34.290 --> 00:41:37.296
I just need to be able to make
my own intuitive decisions

00:41:37.296 --> 00:41:38.670
around food rather
than listening

00:41:38.670 --> 00:41:40.530
to every single
expert that's got

00:41:40.530 --> 00:41:42.120
a different opinion on food.

00:41:42.120 --> 00:41:44.332
I just needed to
block all that out

00:41:44.332 --> 00:41:45.540
to just come home to my body.

00:41:45.540 --> 00:41:47.010
And that really helped me.

00:41:47.010 --> 00:41:48.540
But for sure, it
was a bumpy road.

00:41:48.540 --> 00:41:51.900
And yeah, I realized
along that road

00:41:51.900 --> 00:41:53.630
that veganism wasn't
for me anymore.

00:41:53.630 --> 00:41:56.880
And me deciding to be a vegan--

00:41:56.880 --> 00:42:00.450
my intention behind that
wasn't as it should have been.

00:42:00.450 --> 00:42:02.460
It was because I thought
it was the perfect diet

00:42:02.460 --> 00:42:04.860
and because I thought it
would heal me and make

00:42:04.860 --> 00:42:07.689
me lose weight as opposed
to what actually feels good.

00:42:07.689 --> 00:42:09.480
And I have a lot of
friends that are vegan.

00:42:09.480 --> 00:42:12.700
But they do it for much
more ethical reasons.

00:42:12.700 --> 00:42:15.000
But personally,
for me, I feel good

00:42:15.000 --> 00:42:18.210
when I have a bit of animal
products in my lifestyle.

00:42:18.210 --> 00:42:21.125
And I don't think anyone
should be shamed for that.

